<subSubSection pageId="75" pageNumber="76" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="75" pageNumber="76">Distribution</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="75" pageNumber="76">
(Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 87" captionStartId="F87" captionText="Figure 87. Distribution of Conostegia macrantha." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.67.6703.figure87" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/96445" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">87</figureCitation>
). Endemic to Costa Rica, 1300-3000 m elevation.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-Zenodo-Dep="974213" doi="10.3897/phytokeys.67.6703.figure87" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/96445" pageId="75" pageNumber="76" start="Figure 87" startId="F87">
<paragraph pageId="75" pageNumber="76">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">Figure 87.</emphasis>
Distribution of 
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="O. Berg ex Triana" authorityYear="1871" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia macrantha" order="Myrtales" pageId="75" pageNumber="76" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="macrantha">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">Conostegia macrantha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph pageId="75" pageNumber="76">
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="O. Berg ex Triana" authorityYear="1871" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia macrantha" order="Myrtales" pageId="75" pageNumber="76" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="macrantha">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">Conostegia macrantha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be recognized by its stout branches, stellate indument on abaxial leaf surface, and large flowers with crateriform, straight styles, and retuse petals. Flowers of this species have a good fragrance (i.e., 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Chavarría">Chavarria</normalizedToken>
817
</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Jiménez">Jimenez</normalizedToken>
626
</emphasis>
-both at MO). This species is also reported from northern Panama by 
<bibRefCitation author="Schnell, CE" journalOrPublisher="Harvard University" pageId="243" pageNumber="244" refId="B77" refString="Schnell, CE, 1996. The Genus Conostegia (Melastomataceae). Harvard University" title="The Genus Conostegia (Melastomataceae)" year="1996">Schnell (1996)</bibRefCitation>
but I have not seen any Panamanian specimens. The few specimens from Panama that resemble 
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="O. Berg ex Triana" authorityYear="1871" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia macrantha" order="Myrtales" pageId="75" pageNumber="76" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="macrantha">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">Conostegia macrantha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are glabrous, the reason why I did not include them in the distribution of this species presented here. 
<bibRefCitation author="Schnell, CE" journalOrPublisher="Harvard University" pageId="243" pageNumber="244" refId="B77" refString="Schnell, CE, 1996. The Genus Conostegia (Melastomataceae). Harvard University" title="The Genus Conostegia (Melastomataceae)" year="1996">Schnell (1996)</bibRefCitation>
noted that the species is especially common in the volcanoes surrounding the central valley of Costa Rica and is mostly restricted to that area. Specimens collected near Barva and Poas volcano for this study have the typical straight styles of 
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="O. Berg ex Triana" authorityYear="1871" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia macrantha" order="Myrtales" pageId="75" pageNumber="76" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="macrantha">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">Conostegia macrantha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Schnell, CE" journalOrPublisher="Harvard University" pageId="243" pageNumber="244" refId="B77" refString="Schnell, CE, 1996. The Genus Conostegia (Melastomataceae). Harvard University" title="The Genus Conostegia (Melastomataceae)" year="1996">Schnell (1996)</bibRefCitation>
noted some specimens from Vara Blanca showed evidence of introgression from 
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="O. Berg ex Triana" authorityYear="1871" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia oerstediana" order="Myrtales" pageId="75" pageNumber="76" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="oerstediana">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">Conostegia oerstediana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in their smaller flowers.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
